3.2

Effect of the wall on the motion of bubble swarms

‚Ñ¶ is defined as a vertical circular cylinder bounded by a rigid wall. The size of ‚Ñ¶ is (D‚Ñ¶ , H‚Ñ¶ ) =
(CR ¬∑ d, 4d), where D‚Ñ¶ is the cylinder diameter and H‚Ñ¶ the cylinder height. ‚Ñ¶ is divided in
7.307√ó106 up to 16.592√ó106 triangular-prisms with grid size h = d/40, for CR = 4 and CR = 6
respectively, distributed on 2048 CPU-cores. Non-slip boundary condition is used on the wall,
and periodic boundary condition on the streamwise (y-direction). The bubbles are initially
placed in ‚Ñ¶ following a random pattern, whereas both bubbles and liquid are quiescent. Since
fluid-phases are assumed to be incompressible and coalescence of the bubbles is not allowed,
the void fraction, Œ± = Vbubbles /V‚Ñ¶ , is constant throughout the simulation.
Dimensionless parameters are Eo = 3, M = 10‚àí6 , Œ∑œÅ = 100, Œ∑¬µ = 100, and (Œ±, CR) =
{(8.33%, 6), (12.5%, 4), (10.4%, 4), (8.3%, 4)}, corresponding to dilute bubbly flows with 18, 12,
10 and 8 bubbles. Thus, present simulations are performed with higher Reynolds numbers, as
